# Programming Logic Exercises — Intermediate Level

This repository contains a collection of intermediate-level programming logic exercises designed to improve problem-solving skills and strengthen fundamental programming concepts.

The challenges cover different areas of algorithm development, including conditional statements, loops, number manipulation, sequences, matrices, validations, and interactive programs.

## Objectives

* Improve logical thinking and problem-solving abilities.
* Practice algorithm design and implementation.
* Strengthen the use of control structures.
* Work with different data types and collections.
* Build a foundation for more complex programming projects.

## Exercises Included

* Counting even and odd numbers.
* Finding the highest and lowest values.
* Calculating factorials.
* Checking whether a number is prime.
* Generating the Fibonacci sequence.
* Reversing numbers.
* Student grade classification system.
* Matrix operations.
* Number guessing game.
* ATM withdrawal simulation.

## Technologies

The exercises can be implemented in different programming languages, allowing adaptation to various learning paths and development environments.

## Purpose

This repository is intended for study, practice, and continuous improvement in programming logic. It can be used by students, beginners, and anyone looking to strengthen their algorithmic thinking skills.

